config FB_CBERRY
	tristate "C-Berry LCD frame buffer support"
	depends on FB && SPI && OF
	select FB_SYSMEM_HELPERS_DEFERRED
	select FB_BACKLIGHT
	select BACKLIGHT_CLASS_DEVICE
	help
	  Frame buffer driver for the admatec C-Berry 320x240 LCD module
	  attached to the Raspberry Pi GPIO header.

	  The driver talks to the on-board RAIO8870 LCD controller through
	  the kernel SPI subsystem (spi-bcm2835) and a handful of GPIO
	  descriptors obtained from device tree, which makes it portable
	  across all Raspberry Pi models (Pi 1 through Pi 5).

	  To compile this driver as a module, choose M here. The module
	  will be called cberryfb.
